            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_161gc' title='Col. 161GC &mdash; HL Deb 03 March 2005 vol 670 c161GC' name='column_161gc' href='#column_161gc' rel='bookmark'>161GC</a>
            awful lot in the way of bus stations, publicity, co-ordination of services through tickets and all sorts of things, to make their local transport system more attractive. That is what the electors want in those places; it is not a matter of what the Secretary of State might want.</p><p>
